   <p>For the sake of clarity GW revised this paragraph for his later copyist in this way: Where they come into Service it is with the utmost difficulty they are prevailed upon to take measures for self-defence; much less for the protection of the Inhabitants: But indolent and careless, and always unguarded, are liable to be surprized. By this means Vasss Fort was taken (and the Garrison destroyed) and Dickinsons was on the point of sharing the same fate!</p>

