   <p>GW revealed lingering bitterness, if as it seems, he added this to his letter-book copy years later: And now before I sum up the whole, I must beg leave to addmy unwearied endeavours are inadequately rewardedThe Orders I receive are full of ambiguity: I am left like a wanderer in a wilderness, to proceed at hazardI am answerable for consequences, and blamed, without the priviledge of Defence! It is possible, however, that this passage was in the original letter book and that GW thought better of it and deleted it from the copy he sent to Loudoun.</p>

