</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0045-fn-0033-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0045-fn-0033">33</a>

   <p>For references to a memorial signed by GW and his officers with regard
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-04-02-pb-0093">[93]</span>
to making the Virginia Regiment a part of the regular British army in America, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-03-02-0008&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-03-02-0008-fn-0004#GEWN-02-03-02-0008-fn-0004" class="document">John Robinson to GW, 17 April 1756, n.4</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-03-02-0078&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-03-02-0078-fn-0004#GEWN-02-03-02-0078-fn-0004" class="document">3 May 1756, n.4</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0045-fn-0034-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0045-fn-0034">34</a>

   <p>This portion has been changed to read: The sinews of war, and these only, want your Lordships ability and experience to be properly applied and directed.</p>

</div>
